# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

The library already has model-level support for vision-language models (VLMs) via
`AutoModelForImageTextToText` (defined in `src/models.js`), which covers LLaVA, Qwen2-VL,
Idefics3, SmolVLM, Florence2, PaliGemma, and others. However, no pipeline task wires these
together for end-users. This plan adds the `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class and registers it
in `SUPPORTED_TASKS`, filling that gap and making VLM inference accessible through the
standard `pipeline()` API.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `src/pipelines.js` | **Only file to modify.** Contains all pipeline classes, SUPPORTED_TASKS, and the `pipeline()` factory. |
| `src/models.js` (read-only) | `AutoModelForImageTextToText` already exported at line 8736. |
| `src/base/processing_utils.js` (read-only) | `Processor` base class; has `batch_decode()` (proxies to embedded tokenizer) and `apply_chat_template()` at lines 86–117. |
| `src/models/llava/processing_llava.js` (read-only) | LLaVA: `_call(images, text, kwargs)` — images-first. |
| `src/models/qwen2_vl/processing_qwen2_vl.js` (read-only) | Qwen2-VL: `_call(text, images, ...args)` — text-first. |
| `src/models/idefics3/processing_idefics3.js` (read-only) | Idefics3/SmolVLM: `_call(text, images, options)` — text-first. |

---

## Reusable Utilities (Do Not Recreate)

- `prepareImages(images)` — already defined in `src/pipelines.js` at line 91; normalises any
  `ImagePipelineInputs` to `RawImage[]`.
- `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` typedef — already defined at line 215.
- `Processor.batch_decode()` — proxies to embedded tokenizer; safe to call as
  `this.processor.batch_decode(...)`.

---

## Processor Calling Convention Note

Newer VLMs (Qwen2-VL, Idefics3, SmolVLM — the primary targets) all use
`processor._call(text, images)` — **text first**. The pipeline calls the processor with
`(text, preparedImages)` to match the majority of supported models. LLaVA uses the opposite
order; users of LLaVA should be aware of this difference and can pass pre-processed inputs
via `generate_kwargs` if needed.

---

## Implementation Steps (all changes are in `src/pipelines.js`)

### Step 1 — Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` import

In the existing `import { ... } from './models.js'` block (lines 16–45), add
`AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the named imports list, alongside the other
`AutoModelFor*` imports.

```js
// After AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction, add:
AutoModelForImageTextToText,
```

### Step 2 — Add JSDoc typedefs (insert before the class, after line ~2779)

Place these typedefs immediately after the `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` class closing
brace (~line 2779) and before the `TextToAudioPipeline` typedefs block:

```js
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Generate text from the image(s) and text prompt(s).
 * @param {ImagePipelineInputs} images The input image(s).
 * @param {string|string[]} text The text prompt(s) to condition the generation on.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments to pass along to the generate method of the model.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput|ImageTextToTextOutput[]>} An array or object containing the generated text(s).
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */
```

### Step 3 — Add the pipeline class (insert right after the typedefs from Step 2)

```js
/**
 * Image-text-to-text pipeline using any `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline
 * accepts an image and a text prompt, and generates text conditioned on both.
 *
 * **Example:** Generate a description with `HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct`.
 * ```javascript
 * import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';
 *
 * const generator = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
 * const image = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/huggingface/documentation-images/resolve/main/transformers/tasks/car.jpg';
 * const output = await generator(image, '<image>What is shown in this image?');
 * // [{ generated_text: 'A red sports car ...' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(images, text, generate_kwargs = {}) {
        const isBatched = Array.isArray(images);
        const preparedImages = await prepareImages(images);

        if (!Array.isArray(text)) {
            text = [text];
        }

        // Process images and text together through the processor.
        // The processor handles image feature extraction and text tokenization,
        // including expanding image tokens in the text based on image dimensions.
        const model_inputs = await this.processor(text, preparedImages);

        // Generate output token ids
        const output_ids = /** @type {Tensor} */ (await this.model.generate({
            ...model_inputs,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        }));

        // Decode using the tokenizer embedded in the processor
        const decoded = this.processor.batch_decode(output_ids, {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        });

        const toReturn = decoded.map(t => ({ generated_text: t.trim() }));
        return isBatched ? [toReturn] : toReturn;
    }
}
```

### Step 4 — Register in SUPPORTED_TASKS

In the `SUPPORTED_TASKS` object (around line 3244, near the `"image-to-text"` entry), add
the new entry as a peer:

```js
"image-text-to-text": {
    "pipeline": ImageTextToTextPipeline,
    "model": AutoModelForImageTextToText,
    "processor": AutoProcessor,
    "default": {
        "model": "HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct",
    },
    "type": "multimodal",
},
```

No separate `"tokenizer"` key — the tokenizer is embedded in the processor for all
`AutoModelForImageTextToText` models.

### Step 5 — Update the `pipeline()` JSDoc task list

In the JSDoc for the `pipeline()` function (around line 3418–3441), add a line to the task
list:

```
 *  - `"image-text-to-text"`: will return a `ImageTextToTextPipeline`.
```

